# Acceptance-Oracle Map — {{FEATURE_TITLE}}

One row per Requirement ID. Each oracle must pass the quality gate (falsifiable + binary, externally observable, concretely set up — see SKILL § Step 1). No behavior descriptions here; only observable signals, pass/fail criteria, and the fixed observation method.

`observation_method` is one of: `unit-test` | `integration-run` | `tui-check` | `webapp-check` | `debugger-trace` | `benchmark`. `allowed_producers` is a whitelist of `produced_by` values that may supply evidence for this oracle — see SKILL § Invariants for the default mapping. Both fields are fixed here at Step 1 and cannot be changed silently in Step 2.

| Requirement ID | Requirement                        | Observable signal                                     | Pass/fail oracle                                   | observation_method | allowed_producers            |
